        {
          "reviewTitle": "Excellent Quality",
          "reviewText": "This white foundation works great! It goes on opaque. Perfect for costumes and cosplay.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 20, 2026",
          "customer": "Wolf Reviews",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AG3KZN5N4QT4LH4NA7EJGPRWTFZQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "White"
          }
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "great for gothic looks",
          "reviewText": "I use this every time I do my gothic makeup I do have a few recommendations though. This product is very soft which is a blessing and a curse, with just your fingers you can dip into the pan and apply just patting with your fingers, for the best results a larger flat brush and/or a beauty blender helps with a more even application, if you have oily skin like me or are planning to wear this makeup out somewhere I would recommend a primer before application. You will definitely need to use a powder to bake it after applied if you don't want it to smudge/wipe off and transfer everywhere. It has a really good opacity and is easy to build up if you haven't powdered yet (building it up with fingers can be difficult but the brush and/or beauty blender seems to do it just fine)",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2025",
          "customer": "Angel",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AFPTUVXHPXXJXSSNZZHB3GJZUXWA",
